{
  "text": "There is a long list of potential antigens and there is only a limited number of antigens available for detection (Table 1 ). It would be helpful to have panels of antigens for screening, but the value of these panels should be investigated [35 [CITATION_1] . Moreover, we also miss reliable normal values of the specific IgGs [CITATION_2] . It is also not known whether longitudinal monitoring of the specific IgGs has a meaning for evaluation of the disease activity or prognosis of the patient.",
